Hypoallergenic


Hypoallergenic is formulated to reduce ingredient intolerances and can be used for dogs with food allergies or intolerances - showing as either skin or digestive symptoms. The diet can also be used as part of a food elimination trial.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Food elimination trials
  • Food allergy
  • Food intolerance
  • Inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) 
  • Chronic diarrhoea
  • Bacterial growth 
  • Excorine pancreatic insufficiency 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis
  • History of pancreatitis
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


    HYDROLYSED PROTEIN Hydrolysed proteins are proteins that have been broken down into smaller components to create a diet that is highly digestible and less likely to cause an allergic reaction.



 


  SKIN BARRIER A patented exclusive complex (made up of five special nutrients) to support the barrier function of the skin.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Fatty acids to help maintain a healthy digestive system and a healthy skin.



 


    HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) with specific minerals.

Gastro Intestinal


Gastro Intestinal is formulated for the nutritional management of dogs with acute and chronic gastro intestinal disorders. This is achieved through highly digestible ingredients and a high energy content. 


Recommended for (indications):


  • Acute and chronic diarrhoea
  • Inflammatory bowel disease 
  • Maldigestion, malabsorption
  • Convalescence 
  • Bacterial overgrowth
  • Exocrine pancreatic insufficiency 
  • Gastritis
  • Colitis
  • Anorexia 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis or history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia
  • Lymphangiectasia
  • Hepatic encephalopathy 


KEY BENEFITS:


  HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) and specific nutrients.



 


  HIGH ENERGY This formula is high energy reducing the amount of food given per meal.



 


HIGHLY APPETISING Dogs suffering from digestive troubles often show a decreased appetite and weight loss. The right balance of ingredients makes this diet highly appetising for dogs experiencing digestive upsets.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Essential Fatty acids, EPA & DHA, help maintain a healthy digestive system and healthy skin.

Mobility C2P+


Mobility C2P+ is a complete feed for dogs that helps support osteoarthritis.


For your information: Please note that the presence of orange particles on the kibble surface is completely normal; it is due to the presence of turmeric extract.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Helps maintain mobility in dogs
  • Helps support the joints after orthopaedic surgery or trauma

Not recommended for (contra-indications):


  • Puppies under 8 months
  • Lactation

 RECOMMENDATIONS: Follow your vet’s nutritional recommendations.



EXCLUSIVE JOINT COMPLEX


Formulated with the innovative C2P+ Joint Complex comprising tumeric extract, hydrolysed collagen and green tea polyphenols, nutrients known to support joint health and mobility.



SCIENTIFICALLY PROVEN


The active ingredients incorporated into the exclusive C2P+ joint complex have been shown to improve dogs' mobility and quality of life.



EASES MOBILITY MANAGEMENT


An enhanced palatability encourages consumption of vital nutrients to assist with the daily management of the clinical signs of osteoarthritis.



MODERATE CALORIE


Moderate calorie content to help maintain an ideal body weight. Excessive weight can add further strain to already stressed joints.

Mô tả:
Cardiac


Cardiac is a complete diet for adult dogs to support heart function in the case of chronic cardiac disease. This diet contains a low level of sodium and increased potassium.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Congestive cardiac failure 
  • Hypertension

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pregnancy 
  • Lactation
  • Growth
  • Hyponatraemia
  • Pancreatitis or a history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


  VASCULAR SUPPORT Supports renal filtration by helping facilitate dilation of small blood vessels in the kidneys and therefore reducing pressure in the filteration unit (the Glomerulus). 



 


  EARLY RENAL SUPPORT Heart disease often increases the work load on the kidneys. A moderate phosphorus content will help maintain renal function in dogs with heart disease.



 


  ELECTROLYTE BALANCE Includes electrolytes to support heart function as electrolyte imbalances can have a detrimental effect on the management of cardiac disease.  



 


  CARDIAC SUPPORT Taurine and L-carnitine are included to assist muscle fibre function in the heart, aiding the heart to expand and contract.

Mô tả:
Royal Canin Babydog Milk for puppies from birth to weaning.


Harmonious growth


For steady, harmonious growth, the composition of Babydog milk is as close as possible to bitch’s milk, with high energy and protein levels.


Digestive safety


Babydog milk contains carefully selected ultra-digestible proteins, and has a lactose content very close to that of maternal milk. It is particularly suitable for the puppy’s digestive system, because it does not contain starch, (puppies don’t secrete enough amylase to digest starch). Finally, the addition of Fructo-Oligo-Saccharides (FOS) helps maintain a healthy balance of digestive flora.


Easy to prepare


Thanks to its exclusive formula, Babydog milk dissolves instantly and completely, with no sediment, creating a totally homogenous formula.


Enriched with dha


The puppy’s nervous system continues to develop after birth. DHA naturally present in maternal milk helps develop cognitive function, and so Babydog milk is enriched with DHA.


Composition


Milk proteins, animal fats, whey protein, soya oil, copra oil, fish oil (source of DHA), minerals, fructo-oligo-saccharides. Crude ash: 6%. Crude fibre: 0%. Crude oil fats: 39%. Moisture: 0%. Protein: 33%.


Additives


Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 25000 IU, Vitamin D3: 1500 IU, E1 (Iron): 100 mg, E2 (Iodine): 4 mg, E4 (Copper): 15 mg, E5 (Manganese): 80 mg, E6 (Zinc): 230 mg, E8 (Selenium): 0.43 mg, Taurine: 2.5 g - Antioxidants.


Water should be available at all times.

Mô tả:
A complete dog feed for the small breed bitch (from 1 to 10 kg) and her puppies: bitch at the end of gestation and during lactation, weaning puppies up to 2 months of age.



BIRTH PROGRAMME


Inspired by Professional research, the BIRTH PROGRAMME is a unique nutritional solution which meets the needs of the bitch and her puppies during the first five stages of their life cycle: gestation, birth, lactation, weaning, and growth up to 2 months of age.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


The fruit of ongoing science from Royal Canin, START COMPLEX is an exclusive combination of nutritional elements which are present in mother’s milk, reinforced with specific nutrients which actively contribute to promoting digestive health and supporting the puppy’s natural defences.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


A nutritional profile which is adapted to the bitch’s high energy needs at the end of gestation and during lactation.



IDEAL FOR TRANSITION FROM MILK


A nutritional response which facilitates the transition from mother’s milk to solid food (energy value, quality protein, fats), due to the rehydratable capacity of this diets kibbles.



EASY REHYDRATION


The kibbles easily rehydrate to a porridge-like consistency which is very palatable for the bitch and her weaning puppies.

ĐẶC TÍNH NỔI BẬT

Sự kết hợp của inositol, choline, histidine và axit pantothenic giúp giảm mất nước qua da và tăng cường sự bảo vệ của da.


Axit béo Omega-3 chuỗi dài và các axit điều chỉnh các phản ứng da và giúp bảo vệ niêm mạc ruột.


Kết hợp các protein dễ tiêu hóa, dầu cá, Prebiotics, bột củ cải đường và gạo để đảm bảo sức khỏe tiêu hóa tối đa.

KHẨU PHẦN ĂN


Chó con



Chó trưởng thành


--------------------------------------------


Hypoallergenic


Hypoallergenic is formulated to reduce ingredient intolerances and can be used for dogs with food allergies or intolerances - showing as either skin or digestive symptoms. The diet can also be used as part of a food elimination trial.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Food elimination trials
  • Food allergy
  • Food intolerance
  • Inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) 
  • Chronic diarrhoea
  • Bacterial growth 
  • Excorine pancreatic insufficiency 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis
  • History of pancreatitis
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


    HYDROLYSED PROTEIN Hydrolysed proteins are proteins that have been broken down into smaller components to create a diet that is highly digestible and less likely to cause an allergic reaction.



 


  SKIN BARRIER A patented exclusive complex (made up of five special nutrients) to support the barrier function of the skin.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Fatty acids to help maintain a healthy digestive system and a healthy skin.



 


    HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) with specific minerals.

Mật độ năng lượng cao giúp đáp ứng nhu cầu năng lượng của chó trong khi giảm lượng thức ăn, giảm tiêu hóa, phục hồi cân nặng.


Chó bị bệnh tiêu hóa thường chán ăn và giảm cân. Thức ăn ngon kích thích ăn uống do đó tạo điều kiện phục hồi.


Eicosapentaenoic và docosahexaenoic acid, omega-3 axit béo chuỗi dài, giúp tăng cường sức khỏe hệ tiêu hóa.


Chỉ định


  • Tiêu chảy cấp và mãn tín;
  • Bệnh viêm ruột (BID);
  • Maldigestion, kém hấp thu;
  • Điều dưỡng, phục hồi;
  • Phát triển vi khuẩn quá mức;
  • Suy ngoại tuyến tụy (EPI);
  • Viêm dạ dày;
  • Viêm đại tràng;
  • Biếng ăn.

Chống chỉ định


  • Viêm tụy, có tiền sử viêm tụy;
  • Hyperlipidaemia;
  • Lymphagiectasia.

Gastro Intestinal


Gastro Intestinal is formulated for the nutritional management of dogs with acute and chronic gastro intestinal disorders. This is achieved through highly digestible ingredients and a high energy content. 


Recommended for (indications):


  • Acute and chronic diarrhoea
  • Inflammatory bowel disease 
  • Maldigestion, malabsorption
  • Convalescence 
  • Bacterial overgrowth
  • Exocrine pancreatic insufficiency 
  • Gastritis
  • Colitis
  • Anorexia 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis or history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia
  • Lymphangiectasia
  • Hepatic encephalopathy 


KEY BENEFITS:


  HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) and specific nutrients.



 


  HIGH ENERGY This formula is high energy reducing the amount of food given per meal.



 


HIGHLY APPETISING Dogs suffering from digestive troubles often show a decreased appetite and weight loss. The right balance of ingredients makes this diet highly appetising for dogs experiencing digestive upsets.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Essential Fatty acids, EPA & DHA, help maintain a healthy digestive system and healthy skin.

Mobility C2P+


Mobility C2P+ is a complete feed for dogs that helps support osteoarthritis.


For your information: Please note that the presence of orange particles on the kibble surface is completely normal; it is due to the presence of turmeric extract.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Helps maintain mobility in dogs
  • Helps support the joints after orthopaedic surgery or trauma

Not recommended for (contra-indications):


  • Puppies under 8 months
  • Lactation

 RECOMMENDATIONS: Follow your vet’s nutritional recommendations.



EXCLUSIVE JOINT COMPLEX


Formulated with the innovative C2P+ Joint Complex comprising tumeric extract, hydrolysed collagen and green tea polyphenols, nutrients known to support joint health and mobility.



SCIENTIFICALLY PROVEN


The active ingredients incorporated into the exclusive C2P+ joint complex have been shown to improve dogs' mobility and quality of life.



EASES MOBILITY MANAGEMENT


An enhanced palatability encourages consumption of vital nutrients to assist with the daily management of the clinical signs of osteoarthritis.



MODERATE CALORIE


Moderate calorie content to help maintain an ideal body weight. Excessive weight can add further strain to already stressed joints.

Cardiac


Cardiac is a complete diet for adult dogs to support heart function in the case of chronic cardiac disease. This diet contains a low level of sodium and increased potassium.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Congestive cardiac failure 
  • Hypertension

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pregnancy 
  • Lactation
  • Growth
  • Hyponatraemia
  • Pancreatitis or a history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


  VASCULAR SUPPORT Supports renal filtration by helping facilitate dilation of small blood vessels in the kidneys and therefore reducing pressure in the filteration unit (the Glomerulus). 



 


  EARLY RENAL SUPPORT Heart disease often increases the work load on the kidneys. A moderate phosphorus content will help maintain renal function in dogs with heart disease.



 


  ELECTROLYTE BALANCE Includes electrolytes to support heart function as electrolyte imbalances can have a detrimental effect on the management of cardiac disease.  



 


  CARDIAC SUPPORT Taurine and L-carnitine are included to assist muscle fibre function in the heart, aiding the heart to expand and contract.

Mô tả:
Royal Canin Babydog Milk for puppies from birth to weaning.


Harmonious growth


For steady, harmonious growth, the composition of Babydog milk is as close as possible to bitch’s milk, with high energy and protein levels.


Digestive safety


Babydog milk contains carefully selected ultra-digestible proteins, and has a lactose content very close to that of maternal milk. It is particularly suitable for the puppy’s digestive system, because it does not contain starch, (puppies don’t secrete enough amylase to digest starch). Finally, the addition of Fructo-Oligo-Saccharides (FOS) helps maintain a healthy balance of digestive flora.


Easy to prepare


Thanks to its exclusive formula, Babydog milk dissolves instantly and completely, with no sediment, creating a totally homogenous formula.


Enriched with dha


The puppy’s nervous system continues to develop after birth. DHA naturally present in maternal milk helps develop cognitive function, and so Babydog milk is enriched with DHA.


Composition


Milk proteins, animal fats, whey protein, soya oil, copra oil, fish oil (source of DHA), minerals, fructo-oligo-saccharides. Crude ash: 6%. Crude fibre: 0%. Crude oil fats: 39%. Moisture: 0%. Protein: 33%.


Additives


Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 25000 IU, Vitamin D3: 1500 IU, E1 (Iron): 100 mg, E2 (Iodine): 4 mg, E4 (Copper): 15 mg, E5 (Manganese): 80 mg, E6 (Zinc): 230 mg, E8 (Selenium): 0.43 mg, Taurine: 2.5 g - Antioxidants.


Water should be available at all times.

Mô tả:
A complete dog feed for the small breed bitch (from 1 to 10 kg) and her puppies: bitch at the end of gestation and during lactation, weaning puppies up to 2 months of age.



BIRTH PROGRAMME


Inspired by Professional research, the BIRTH PROGRAMME is a unique nutritional solution which meets the needs of the bitch and her puppies during the first five stages of their life cycle: gestation, birth, lactation, weaning, and growth up to 2 months of age.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


The fruit of ongoing science from Royal Canin, START COMPLEX is an exclusive combination of nutritional elements which are present in mother’s milk, reinforced with specific nutrients which actively contribute to promoting digestive health and supporting the puppy’s natural defences.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


A nutritional profile which is adapted to the bitch’s high energy needs at the end of gestation and during lactation.



IDEAL FOR TRANSITION FROM MILK


A nutritional response which facilitates the transition from mother’s milk to solid food (energy value, quality protein, fats), due to the rehydratable capacity of this diets kibbles.



EASY REHYDRATION


The kibbles easily rehydrate to a porridge-like consistency which is very palatable for the bitch and her weaning puppies.

Hypoallergenic


Hypoallergenic is formulated to reduce ingredient intolerances and can be used for dogs with food allergies or intolerances - showing as either skin or digestive symptoms. The diet can also be used as part of a food elimination trial.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Food elimination trials
  • Food allergy
  • Food intolerance
  • Inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) 
  • Chronic diarrhoea
  • Bacterial growth 
  • Excorine pancreatic insufficiency 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis
  • History of pancreatitis
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


    HYDROLYSED PROTEIN Hydrolysed proteins are proteins that have been broken down into smaller components to create a diet that is highly digestible and less likely to cause an allergic reaction.



 


  SKIN BARRIER A patented exclusive complex (made up of five special nutrients) to support the barrier function of the skin.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Fatty acids to help maintain a healthy digestive system and a healthy skin.



 


    HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) with specific minerals.

Gastro Intestinal


Gastro Intestinal is formulated for the nutritional management of dogs with acute and chronic gastro intestinal disorders. This is achieved through highly digestible ingredients and a high energy content. 


Recommended for (indications):


  • Acute and chronic diarrhoea
  • Inflammatory bowel disease 
  • Maldigestion, malabsorption
  • Convalescence 
  • Bacterial overgrowth
  • Exocrine pancreatic insufficiency 
  • Gastritis
  • Colitis
  • Anorexia 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis or history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia
  • Lymphangiectasia
  • Hepatic encephalopathy 


KEY BENEFITS:


  HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) and specific nutrients.



 


  HIGH ENERGY This formula is high energy reducing the amount of food given per meal.



 


HIGHLY APPETISING Dogs suffering from digestive troubles often show a decreased appetite and weight loss. The right balance of ingredients makes this diet highly appetising for dogs experiencing digestive upsets.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Essential Fatty acids, EPA & DHA, help maintain a healthy digestive system and healthy skin.

ĐẶC TÍNH NỔI BẬT

Mô tả:
ĐẶC TÍNH NỔI BẬT


Chiết xuất trai miệng xanh New Zealand với tiền chất sụn để giúp duy trì khớp khỏe mạnh.


EPA/DHA giúp hỗ trợ thêm để duy trì sức khỏe của xương khớp.


Hàm lượng calo vừa phải giúp duy trì cân nặng lý tưởng và giảm cân nặng dư thừa gây áp lực cho khớp.


Sự kết hợp của các hệ dưỡng chất chống oxy hóa giúp giảm áp lực oxy hóa và chống lại các gốc tự do.


Chỉ định


  • Giúp duy trì tính di động ở chó;

Not recommended for (contra-indications):


  • Puppies under 8 months
  • Lactation

 RECOMMENDATIONS: Follow your vet’s nutritional recommendations.



EXCLUSIVE JOINT COMPLEX


Formulated with the innovative C2P+ Joint Complex comprising tumeric extract, hydrolysed collagen and green tea polyphenols, nutrients known to support joint health and mobility.



SCIENTIFICALLY PROVEN


The active ingredients incorporated into the exclusive C2P+ joint complex have been shown to improve dogs' mobility and quality of life.



EASES MOBILITY MANAGEMENT


An enhanced palatability encourages consumption of vital nutrients to assist with the daily management of the clinical signs of osteoarthritis.



MODERATE CALORIE


Moderate calorie content to help maintain an ideal body weight. Excessive weight can add further strain to already stressed joints.

Mô tả:
Cardiac


Cardiac is a complete diet for adult dogs to support heart function in the case of chronic cardiac disease. This diet contains a low level of sodium and increased potassium.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Congestive cardiac failure 
  • Hypertension

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pregnancy 
  • Lactation
  • Growth
  • Hyponatraemia
  • Pancreatitis or a history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


  VASCULAR SUPPORT Supports renal filtration by helping facilitate dilation of small blood vessels in the kidneys and therefore reducing pressure in the filteration unit (the Glomerulus). 



 


  EARLY RENAL SUPPORT Heart disease often increases the work load on the kidneys. A moderate phosphorus content will help maintain renal function in dogs with heart disease.



 


  ELECTROLYTE BALANCE Includes electrolytes to support heart function as electrolyte imbalances can have a detrimental effect on the management of cardiac disease.  



 


  CARDIAC SUPPORT Taurine and L-carnitine are included to assist muscle fibre function in the heart, aiding the heart to expand and contract.

Mô tả:
Royal Canin Babydog Milk for puppies from birth to weaning.


Harmonious growth


For steady, harmonious growth, the composition of Babydog milk is as close as possible to bitch’s milk, with high energy and protein levels.


Digestive safety


Babydog milk contains carefully selected ultra-digestible proteins, and has a lactose content very close to that of maternal milk. It is particularly suitable for the puppy’s digestive system, because it does not contain starch, (puppies don’t secrete enough amylase to digest starch). Finally, the addition of Fructo-Oligo-Saccharides (FOS) helps maintain a healthy balance of digestive flora.


Easy to prepare


Thanks to its exclusive formula, Babydog milk dissolves instantly and completely, with no sediment, creating a totally homogenous formula.


Enriched with dha


The puppy’s nervous system continues to develop after birth. DHA naturally present in maternal milk helps develop cognitive function, and so Babydog milk is enriched with DHA.


Composition


Milk proteins, animal fats, whey protein, soya oil, copra oil, fish oil (source of DHA), minerals, fructo-oligo-saccharides. Crude ash: 6%. Crude fibre: 0%. Crude oil fats: 39%. Moisture: 0%. Protein: 33%.


Additives


Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 25000 IU, Vitamin D3: 1500 IU, E1 (Iron): 100 mg, E2 (Iodine): 4 mg, E4 (Copper): 15 mg, E5 (Manganese): 80 mg, E6 (Zinc): 230 mg, E8 (Selenium): 0.43 mg, Taurine: 2.5 g - Antioxidants.


Water should be available at all times.

Mô tả:
A complete dog feed for the small breed bitch (from 1 to 10 kg) and her puppies: bitch at the end of gestation and during lactation, weaning puppies up to 2 months of age.



BIRTH PROGRAMME


Inspired by Professional research, the BIRTH PROGRAMME is a unique nutritional solution which meets the needs of the bitch and her puppies during the first five stages of their life cycle: gestation, birth, lactation, weaning, and growth up to 2 months of age.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


The fruit of ongoing science from Royal Canin, START COMPLEX is an exclusive combination of nutritional elements which are present in mother’s milk, reinforced with specific nutrients which actively contribute to promoting digestive health and supporting the puppy’s natural defences.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


A nutritional profile which is adapted to the bitch’s high energy needs at the end of gestation and during lactation.



IDEAL FOR TRANSITION FROM MILK


A nutritional response which facilitates the transition from mother’s milk to solid food (energy value, quality protein, fats), due to the rehydratable capacity of this diets kibbles.



EASY REHYDRATION


The kibbles easily rehydrate to a porridge-like consistency which is very palatable for the bitch and her weaning puppies.

Hypoallergenic


Hypoallergenic is formulated to reduce ingredient intolerances and can be used for dogs with food allergies or intolerances - showing as either skin or digestive symptoms. The diet can also be used as part of a food elimination trial.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Food elimination trials
  • Food allergy
  • Food intolerance
  • Inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) 
  • Chronic diarrhoea
  • Bacterial growth 
  • Excorine pancreatic insufficiency 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis
  • History of pancreatitis
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


    HYDROLYSED PROTEIN Hydrolysed proteins are proteins that have been broken down into smaller components to create a diet that is highly digestible and less likely to cause an allergic reaction.



 


  SKIN BARRIER A patented exclusive complex (made up of five special nutrients) to support the barrier function of the skin.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Fatty acids to help maintain a healthy digestive system and a healthy skin.



 


    HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) with specific minerals.

Gastro Intestinal


Gastro Intestinal is formulated for the nutritional management of dogs with acute and chronic gastro intestinal disorders. This is achieved through highly digestible ingredients and a high energy content. 


Recommended for (indications):


  • Acute and chronic diarrhoea
  • Inflammatory bowel disease 
  • Maldigestion, malabsorption
  • Convalescence 
  • Bacterial overgrowth
  • Exocrine pancreatic insufficiency 
  • Gastritis
  • Colitis
  • Anorexia 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis or history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia
  • Lymphangiectasia
  • Hepatic encephalopathy 


KEY BENEFITS:


  HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) and specific nutrients.



 


  HIGH ENERGY This formula is high energy reducing the amount of food given per meal.



 


HIGHLY APPETISING Dogs suffering from digestive troubles often show a decreased appetite and weight loss. The right balance of ingredients makes this diet highly appetising for dogs experiencing digestive upsets.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Essential Fatty acids, EPA & DHA, help maintain a healthy digestive system and healthy skin.

Mobility C2P+


Mobility C2P+ is a complete feed for dogs that helps support osteoarthritis.


For your information: Please note that the presence of orange particles on the kibble surface is completely normal; it is due to the presence of turmeric extract.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Helps maintain mobility in dogs
  • Helps support the joints after orthopaedic surgery or trauma

Not recommended for (contra-indications):


  • Puppies under 8 months
  • Lactation

 RECOMMENDATIONS: Follow your vet’s nutritional recommendations.



EXCLUSIVE JOINT COMPLEX


Formulated with the innovative C2P+ Joint Complex comprising tumeric extract, hydrolysed collagen and green tea polyphenols, nutrients known to support joint health and mobility.



SCIENTIFICALLY PROVEN


The active ingredients incorporated into the exclusive C2P+ joint complex have been shown to improve dogs' mobility and quality of life.



EASES MOBILITY MANAGEMENT


An enhanced palatability encourages consumption of vital nutrients to assist with the daily management of the clinical signs of osteoarthritis.



MODERATE CALORIE


Moderate calorie content to help maintain an ideal body weight. Excessive weight can add further strain to already stressed joints.

Mô tả:
Cardiac


Cardiac is a complete diet for adult dogs to support heart function in the case of chronic cardiac disease. This diet contains a low level of sodium and increased potassium.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Congestive cardiac failure 
  • Hypertension

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pregnancy 
  • Lactation
  • Growth
  • Hyponatraemia
  • Pancreatitis or a history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


  VASCULAR SUPPORT Supports renal filtration by helping facilitate dilation of small blood vessels in the kidneys and therefore reducing pressure in the filteration unit (the Glomerulus). 



 


  EARLY RENAL SUPPORT Heart disease often increases the work load on the kidneys. A moderate phosphorus content will help maintain renal function in dogs with heart disease.



 


  ELECTROLYTE BALANCE Includes electrolytes to support heart function as electrolyte imbalances can have a detrimental effect on the management of cardiac disease.  



 


  CARDIAC SUPPORT Taurine and L-carnitine are included to assist muscle fibre function in the heart, aiding the heart to expand and contract.

Mô tả:
Royal Canin Babydog Milk for puppies from birth to weaning.


Harmonious growth


For steady, harmonious growth, the composition of Babydog milk is as close as possible to bitch’s milk, with high energy and protein levels.


Digestive safety


Babydog milk contains carefully selected ultra-digestible proteins, and has a lactose content very close to that of maternal milk. It is particularly suitable for the puppy’s digestive system, because it does not contain starch, (puppies don’t secrete enough amylase to digest starch). Finally, the addition of Fructo-Oligo-Saccharides (FOS) helps maintain a healthy balance of digestive flora.


Easy to prepare


Thanks to its exclusive formula, Babydog milk dissolves instantly and completely, with no sediment, creating a totally homogenous formula.


Enriched with dha


The puppy’s nervous system continues to develop after birth. DHA naturally present in maternal milk helps develop cognitive function, and so Babydog milk is enriched with DHA.


Composition


Milk proteins, animal fats, whey protein, soya oil, copra oil, fish oil (source of DHA), minerals, fructo-oligo-saccharides. Crude ash: 6%. Crude fibre: 0%. Crude oil fats: 39%. Moisture: 0%. Protein: 33%.


Additives


Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 25000 IU, Vitamin D3: 1500 IU, E1 (Iron): 100 mg, E2 (Iodine): 4 mg, E4 (Copper): 15 mg, E5 (Manganese): 80 mg, E6 (Zinc): 230 mg, E8 (Selenium): 0.43 mg, Taurine: 2.5 g - Antioxidants.


Water should be available at all times.

Mô tả:
A complete dog feed for the small breed bitch (from 1 to 10 kg) and her puppies: bitch at the end of gestation and during lactation, weaning puppies up to 2 months of age.



BIRTH PROGRAMME


Inspired by Professional research, the BIRTH PROGRAMME is a unique nutritional solution which meets the needs of the bitch and her puppies during the first five stages of their life cycle: gestation, birth, lactation, weaning, and growth up to 2 months of age.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


The fruit of ongoing science from Royal Canin, START COMPLEX is an exclusive combination of nutritional elements which are present in mother’s milk, reinforced with specific nutrients which actively contribute to promoting digestive health and supporting the puppy’s natural defences.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


A nutritional profile which is adapted to the bitch’s high energy needs at the end of gestation and during lactation.



IDEAL FOR TRANSITION FROM MILK


A nutritional response which facilitates the transition from mother’s milk to solid food (energy value, quality protein, fats), due to the rehydratable capacity of this diets kibbles.



EASY REHYDRATION


The kibbles easily rehydrate to a porridge-like consistency which is very palatable for the bitch and her weaning puppies.

Hypoallergenic


Hypoallergenic is formulated to reduce ingredient intolerances and can be used for dogs with food allergies or intolerances - showing as either skin or digestive symptoms. The diet can also be used as part of a food elimination trial.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Food elimination trials
  • Food allergy
  • Food intolerance
  • Inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) 
  • Chronic diarrhoea
  • Bacterial growth 
  • Excorine pancreatic insufficiency 

Not recommended for (contraindications):

Mobility C2P+


Mobility C2P+ is a complete feed for dogs that helps support osteoarthritis.


For your information: Please note that the presence of orange particles on the kibble surface is completely normal; it is due to the presence of turmeric extract.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Helps maintain mobility in dogs
  • Helps support the joints after orthopaedic surgery or trauma

Not recommended for (contra-indications):


  • Puppies under 8 months
  • Lactation

 RECOMMENDATIONS: Follow your vet’s nutritional recommendations.



EXCLUSIVE JOINT COMPLEX


Formulated with the innovative C2P+ Joint Complex comprising tumeric extract, hydrolysed collagen and green tea polyphenols, nutrients known to support joint health and mobility.



SCIENTIFICALLY PROVEN


The active ingredients incorporated into the exclusive C2P+ joint complex have been shown to improve dogs' mobility and quality of life.



EASES MOBILITY MANAGEMENT


An enhanced palatability encourages consumption of vital nutrients to assist with the daily management of the clinical signs of osteoarthritis.



MODERATE CALORIE


Moderate calorie content to help maintain an ideal body weight. Excessive weight can add further strain to already stressed joints.

Cardiac


Cardiac is a complete diet for adult dogs to support heart function in the case of chronic cardiac disease. This diet contains a low level of sodium and increased potassium.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Congestive cardiac failure 
  • Hypertension

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pregnancy 
  • Lactation
  • Growth
  • Hyponatraemia
  • Pancreatitis or a history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


  VASCULAR SUPPORT Supports renal filtration by helping facilitate dilation of small blood vessels in the kidneys and therefore reducing pressure in the filteration unit (the Glomerulus). 



 


  EARLY RENAL SUPPORT Heart disease often increases the work load on the kidneys. A moderate phosphorus content will help maintain renal function in dogs with heart disease.



 


  ELECTROLYTE BALANCE Includes electrolytes to support heart function as electrolyte imbalances can have a detrimental effect on the management of cardiac disease.  



 


  CARDIAC SUPPORT Taurine and L-carnitine are included to assist muscle fibre function in the heart, aiding the heart to expand and contract.

Mô tả:
Royal Canin Babydog Milk for puppies from birth to weaning.


Harmonious growth


For steady, harmonious growth, the composition of Babydog milk is as close as possible to bitch’s milk, with high energy and protein levels.


Digestive safety


Babydog milk contains carefully selected ultra-digestible proteins, and has a lactose content very close to that of maternal milk. It is particularly suitable for the puppy’s digestive system, because it does not contain starch, (puppies don’t secrete enough amylase to digest starch). Finally, the addition of Fructo-Oligo-Saccharides (FOS) helps maintain a healthy balance of digestive flora.


Easy to prepare


Thanks to its exclusive formula, Babydog milk dissolves instantly and completely, with no sediment, creating a totally homogenous formula.


Enriched with dha


The puppy’s nervous system continues to develop after birth. DHA naturally present in maternal milk helps develop cognitive function, and so Babydog milk is enriched with DHA.


Composition


Milk proteins, animal fats, whey protein, soya oil, copra oil, fish oil (source of DHA), minerals, fructo-oligo-saccharides. Crude ash: 6%. Crude fibre: 0%. Crude oil fats: 39%. Moisture: 0%. Protein: 33%.


Additives


Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 25000 IU, Vitamin D3: 1500 IU, E1 (Iron): 100 mg, E2 (Iodine): 4 mg, E4 (Copper): 15 mg, E5 (Manganese): 80 mg, E6 (Zinc): 230 mg, E8 (Selenium): 0.43 mg, Taurine: 2.5 g - Antioxidants.

Mô tả:
A complete dog feed for the small breed bitch (from 1 to 10 kg) and her puppies: bitch at the end of gestation and during lactation, weaning puppies up to 2 months of age.



BIRTH PROGRAMME


Inspired by Professional research, the BIRTH PROGRAMME is a unique nutritional solution which meets the needs of the bitch and her puppies during the first five stages of their life cycle: gestation, birth, lactation, weaning, and growth up to 2 months of age.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


The fruit of ongoing science from Royal Canin, START COMPLEX is an exclusive combination of nutritional elements which are present in mother’s milk, reinforced with specific nutrients which actively contribute to promoting digestive health and supporting the puppy’s natural defences.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


A nutritional profile which is adapted to the bitch’s high energy needs at the end of gestation and during lactation.



IDEAL FOR TRANSITION FROM MILK


A nutritional response which facilitates the transition from mother’s milk to solid food (energy value, quality protein, fats), due to the rehydratable capacity of this diets kibbles.



EASY REHYDRATION


The kibbles easily rehydrate to a porridge-like consistency which is very palatable for the bitch and her weaning puppies.

ĐẶC TÍNH NỔI BẬT


Protein đậu nành được thủy phân bao gồm các Peptide có phân tử lượng thấp dễ tiêu hóa và ít gây dị ứng nhất.


Sự kết hợp của inositol, choline, histidine và axit pantothenic giúp giảm mất nước qua da và tăng cường sự bảo vệ của da.


Axit béo Omega-3 chuỗi dài và các axit điều chỉnh các phản ứng da và giúp bảo vệ niêm mạc ruột.


Kết hợp các protein dễ tiêu hóa, dầu cá, Prebiotics, bột củ cải đường và gạo để đảm bảo sức khỏe tiêu hóa tối đa.

Chó con



Chó trưởng thành

Hypoallergenic


Hypoallergenic is formulated to reduce ingredient intolerances and can be used for dogs with food allergies or intolerances - showing as either skin or digestive symptoms. The diet can also be used as part of a food elimination trial.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Food elimination trials
  • Food allergy
  • Food intolerance
  • Inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) 
  • Chronic diarrhoea
  • Bacterial growth 
  • Excorine pancreatic insufficiency 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis
  • History of pancreatitis
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


    HYDROLYSED PROTEIN Hydrolysed proteins are proteins that have been broken down into smaller components to create a diet that is highly digestible and less likely to cause an allergic reaction.



 


  SKIN BARRIER A patented exclusive complex (made up of five special nutrients) to support the barrier function of the skin.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Fatty acids to help maintain a healthy digestive system and a healthy skin.



 


    HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) with specific minerals.

Gastro Intestinal


Gastro Intestinal is formulated for the nutritional management of dogs with acute and chronic gastro intestinal disorders. This is achieved through highly digestible ingredients and a high energy content. 


Recommended for (indications):


  • Acute and chronic diarrhoea
  • Inflammatory bowel disease 
  • Maldigestion, malabsorption
  • Convalescence 
  • Bacterial overgrowth
  • Exocrine pancreatic insufficiency 
  • Gastritis
  • Colitis
  • Anorexia 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis or history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia
  • Lymphangiectasia
  • Hepatic encephalopathy 


KEY BENEFITS:


  HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) and specific nutrients.



 


  HIGH ENERGY This formula is high energy reducing the amount of food given per meal.



 


HIGHLY APPETISING Dogs suffering from digestive troubles often show a decreased appetite and weight loss. The right balance of ingredients makes this diet highly appetising for dogs experiencing digestive upsets.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Essential Fatty acids, EPA & DHA, help maintain a healthy digestive system and healthy skin.

Mobility C2P+


Mobility C2P+ is a complete feed for dogs that helps support osteoarthritis.


For your information: Please note that the presence of orange particles on the kibble surface is completely normal; it is due to the presence of turmeric extract.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Helps maintain mobility in dogs
  • Helps support the joints after orthopaedic surgery or trauma

Not recommended for (contra-indications):


  • Puppies under 8 months
  • Lactation

 RECOMMENDATIONS: Follow your vet’s nutritional recommendations.



EXCLUSIVE JOINT COMPLEX


Formulated with the innovative C2P+ Joint Complex comprising tumeric extract, hydrolysed collagen and green tea polyphenols, nutrients known to support joint health and mobility.



SCIENTIFICALLY PROVEN


The active ingredients incorporated into the exclusive C2P+ joint complex have been shown to improve dogs' mobility and quality of life.



EASES MOBILITY MANAGEMENT


An enhanced palatability encourages consumption of vital nutrients to assist with the daily management of the clinical signs of osteoarthritis.



MODERATE CALORIE


Moderate calorie content to help maintain an ideal body weight. Excessive weight can add further strain to already stressed joints.

Mô tả:
Cardiac


Cardiac is a complete diet for adult dogs to support heart function in the case of chronic cardiac disease. This diet contains a low level of sodium and increased potassium.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Congestive cardiac failure 
  • Hypertension

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pregnancy 
  • Lactation
  • Growth
  • Hyponatraemia
  • Pancreatitis or a history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


  VASCULAR SUPPORT Supports renal filtration by helping facilitate dilation of small blood vessels in the kidneys and therefore reducing pressure in the filteration unit (the Glomerulus). 



 


  EARLY RENAL SUPPORT Heart disease often increases the work load on the kidneys. A moderate phosphorus content will help maintain renal function in dogs with heart disease.



 


  ELECTROLYTE BALANCE Includes electrolytes to support heart function as electrolyte imbalances can have a detrimental effect on the management of cardiac disease.  



 


  CARDIAC SUPPORT Taurine and L-carnitine are included to assist muscle fibre function in the heart, aiding the heart to expand and contract.

Mô tả:
Royal Canin Babydog Milk for puppies from birth to weaning.


Harmonious growth


For steady, harmonious growth, the composition of Babydog milk is as close as possible to bitch’s milk, with high energy and protein levels.


Digestive safety


Babydog milk contains carefully selected ultra-digestible proteins, and has a lactose content very close to that of maternal milk. It is particularly suitable for the puppy’s digestive system, because it does not contain starch, (puppies don’t secrete enough amylase to digest starch). Finally, the addition of Fructo-Oligo-Saccharides (FOS) helps maintain a healthy balance of digestive flora.


Easy to prepare


Thanks to its exclusive formula, Babydog milk dissolves instantly and completely, with no sediment, creating a totally homogenous formula.


Enriched with dha


The puppy’s nervous system continues to develop after birth. DHA naturally present in maternal milk helps develop cognitive function, and so Babydog milk is enriched with DHA.


Composition


Milk proteins, animal fats, whey protein, soya oil, copra oil, fish oil (source of DHA), minerals, fructo-oligo-saccharides. Crude ash: 6%. Crude fibre: 0%. Crude oil fats: 39%. Moisture: 0%. Protein: 33%.


Additives


Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 25000 IU, Vitamin D3: 1500 IU, E1 (Iron): 100 mg, E2 (Iodine): 4 mg, E4 (Copper): 15 mg, E5 (Manganese): 80 mg, E6 (Zinc): 230 mg, E8 (Selenium): 0.43 mg, Taurine: 2.5 g - Antioxidants.


Water should be available at all times.

Tên: Royal Canin Mini Starter Mother & Baby Dog 3kg
Mô tả ngắn:
Thức ăn dành cho chó mẹ & con, giống chó giống nhỏ (Mini)


Mini là giống chó lớn có trọng lượng khi trưởng thành từ 1-10kg


Dùng khi chó mẹ đang mang thai, đang cho con bú, chó con đang tập ăn từ 1 - 2 tháng tuổi


Bổ sung dưỡng chất phù hợp với giai đoạn phát triển đầu đời của chó con


Sản phẩm của Royal Canin, sản xuất tại Pháp
Mô tả:
A complete dog feed for the small breed bitch (from 1 to 10 kg) and her puppies: bitch at the end of gestation and during lactation, weaning puppies up to 2 months of age.



BIRTH PROGRAMME


Inspired by Professional research, the BIRTH PROGRAMME is a unique nutritional solution which meets the needs of the bitch and her puppies during the first five stages of their life cycle: gestation, birth, lactation, weaning, and growth up to 2 months of age.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


The fruit of ongoing science from Royal Canin, START COMPLEX is an exclusive combination of nutritional elements which are present in mother’s milk, reinforced with specific nutrients which actively contribute to promoting digestive health and supporting the puppy’s natural defences.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


A nutritional profile which is adapted to the bitch’s high energy needs at the end of gestation and during lactation.



IDEAL FOR TRANSITION FROM MILK


A nutritional response which facilitates the transition from mother’s milk to solid food (energy value, quality protein, fats), due to the rehydratable capacity of this diets kibbles.



EASY REHYDRATION


The kibbles easily rehydrate to a porridge-like consistency which is very palatable for the bitch and her weaning puppies.

Hypoallergenic


Hypoallergenic is formulated to reduce ingredient intolerances and can be used for dogs with food allergies or intolerances - showing as either skin or digestive symptoms. The diet can also be used as part of a food elimination trial.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Food elimination trials
  • Food allergy
  • Food intolerance
  • Inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) 
  • Chronic diarrhoea
  • Bacterial growth 
  • Excorine pancreatic insufficiency 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis
  • History of pancreatitis
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


    HYDROLYSED PROTEIN Hydrolysed proteins are proteins that have been broken down into smaller components to create a diet that is highly digestible and less likely to cause an allergic reaction.



 


  SKIN BARRIER A patented exclusive complex (made up of five special nutrients) to support the barrier function of the skin.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Fatty acids to help maintain a healthy digestive system and a healthy skin.



 


    HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) with specific minerals.

Gastro Intestinal


Gastro Intestinal is formulated for the nutritional management of dogs with acute and chronic gastro intestinal disorders. This is achieved through highly digestible ingredients and a high energy content. 


Recommended for (indications):


  • Acute and chronic diarrhoea
  • Inflammatory bowel disease 
  • Maldigestion, malabsorption
  • Convalescence 
  • Bacterial overgrowth
  • Exocrine pancreatic insufficiency 
  • Gastritis
  • Colitis
  • Anorexia 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis or history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia
  • Lymphangiectasia
  • Hepatic encephalopathy 


KEY BENEFITS:


  HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) and specific nutrients.



 


  HIGH ENERGY This formula is high energy reducing the amount of food given per meal.



 


HIGHLY APPETISING Dogs suffering from digestive troubles often show a decreased appetite and weight loss. The right balance of ingredients makes this diet highly appetising for dogs experiencing digestive upsets.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Essential Fatty acids, EPA & DHA, help maintain a healthy digestive system and healthy skin.

Mobility C2P+


Mobility C2P+ is a complete feed for dogs that helps support osteoarthritis.


For your information: Please note that the presence of orange particles on the kibble surface is completely normal; it is due to the presence of turmeric extract.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Helps maintain mobility in dogs
  • Helps support the joints after orthopaedic surgery or trauma

Not recommended for (contra-indications):


  • Puppies under 8 months
  • Lactation

 RECOMMENDATIONS: Follow your vet’s nutritional recommendations.



EXCLUSIVE JOINT COMPLEX


Formulated with the innovative C2P+ Joint Complex comprising tumeric extract, hydrolysed collagen and green tea polyphenols, nutrients known to support joint health and mobility.



SCIENTIFICALLY PROVEN


The active ingredients incorporated into the exclusive C2P+ joint complex have been shown to improve dogs' mobility and quality of life.



EASES MOBILITY MANAGEMENT


An enhanced palatability encourages consumption of vital nutrients to assist with the daily management of the clinical signs of osteoarthritis.



MODERATE CALORIE


Moderate calorie content to help maintain an ideal body weight. Excessive weight can add further strain to already stressed joints.

Mô tả:
Cardiac


Cardiac is a complete diet for adult dogs to support heart function in the case of chronic cardiac disease. This diet contains a low level of sodium and increased potassium.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Congestive cardiac failure 
  • Hypertension

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pregnancy 
  • Lactation
  • Growth
  • Hyponatraemia
  • Pancreatitis or a history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


  VASCULAR SUPPORT Supports renal filtration by helping facilitate dilation of small blood vessels in the kidneys and therefore reducing pressure in the filteration unit (the Glomerulus). 



 


  EARLY RENAL SUPPORT Heart disease often increases the work load on the kidneys. A moderate phosphorus content will help maintain renal function in dogs with heart disease.



 


  ELECTROLYTE BALANCE Includes electrolytes to support heart function as electrolyte imbalances can have a detrimental effect on the management of cardiac disease.  



 


  CARDIAC SUPPORT Taurine and L-carnitine are included to assist muscle fibre function in the heart, aiding the heart to expand and contract.

Mô tả:
Royal Canin Babydog Milk for puppies from birth to weaning.


Harmonious growth


For steady, harmonious growth, the composition of Babydog milk is as close as possible to bitch’s milk, with high energy and protein levels.


Digestive safety


Babydog milk contains carefully selected ultra-digestible proteins, and has a lactose content very close to that of maternal milk. It is particularly suitable for the puppy’s digestive system, because it does not contain starch, (puppies don’t secrete enough amylase to digest starch). Finally, the addition of Fructo-Oligo-Saccharides (FOS) helps maintain a healthy balance of digestive flora.


Easy to prepare


Thanks to its exclusive formula, Babydog milk dissolves instantly and completely, with no sediment, creating a totally homogenous formula.


Enriched with dha


The puppy’s nervous system continues to develop after birth. DHA naturally present in maternal milk helps develop cognitive function, and so Babydog milk is enriched with DHA.


Composition


Milk proteins, animal fats, whey protein, soya oil, copra oil, fish oil (source of DHA), minerals, fructo-oligo-saccharides. Crude ash: 6%. Crude fibre: 0%. Crude oil fats: 39%. Moisture: 0%. Protein: 33%.


Additives


Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 25000 IU, Vitamin D3: 1500 IU, E1 (Iron): 100 mg, E2 (Iodine): 4 mg, E4 (Copper): 15 mg, E5 (Manganese): 80 mg, E6 (Zinc): 230 mg, E8 (Selenium): 0.43 mg, Taurine: 2.5 g - Antioxidants.


Water should be available at all times.

Mô tả:
A complete dog feed for the small breed bitch (from 1 to 10 kg) and her puppies: bitch at the end of gestation and during lactation, weaning puppies up to 2 months of age.



BIRTH PROGRAMME


Inspired by Professional research, the BIRTH PROGRAMME is a unique nutritional solution which meets the needs of the bitch and her puppies during the first five stages of their life cycle: gestation, birth, lactation, weaning, and growth up to 2 months of age.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


The fruit of ongoing science from Royal Canin, START COMPLEX is an exclusive combination of nutritional elements which are present in mother’s milk, reinforced with specific nutrients which actively contribute to promoting digestive health and supporting the puppy’s natural defences.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


A nutritional profile which is adapted to the bitch’s high energy needs at the end of gestation and during lactation.



IDEAL FOR TRANSITION FROM MILK


A nutritional response which facilitates the transition from mother’s milk to solid food (energy value, quality protein, fats), due to the rehydratable capacity of this diets kibbles.



EASY REHYDRATION


The kibbles easily rehydrate to a porridge-like consistency which is very palatable for the bitch and her weaning puppies.

Hypoallergenic


Hypoallergenic is formulated to reduce ingredient intolerances and can be used for dogs with food allergies or intolerances - showing as either skin or digestive symptoms. The diet can also be used as part of a food elimination trial.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Food elimination trials
  • Food allergy
  • Food intolerance
  • Inflammatory bowel disease (IBD) 
  • Chronic diarrhoea
  • Bacterial growth 
  • Excorine pancreatic insufficiency 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis
  • History of pancreatitis
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


    HYDROLYSED PROTEIN Hydrolysed proteins are proteins that have been broken down into smaller components to create a diet that is highly digestible and less likely to cause an allergic reaction.



 


  SKIN BARRIER A patented exclusive complex (made up of five special nutrients) to support the barrier function of the skin.



 


  ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS: EPA/DHA Fatty acids to help maintain a healthy digestive system and a healthy skin.



 


    HEALTHY DIGESTION Helps maintain a healthy digestive system through the combination of fermentable fibres (beet pulp and FOS) with specific minerals.

Gastro Intestinal is formulated for the nutritional management of dogs with acute and chronic gastro intestinal disorders. This is achieved through highly digestible ingredients and a high energy content. 


Recommended for (indications):


  • Acute and chronic diarrhoea
  • Inflammatory bowel disease 
  • Maldigestion, malabsorption
  • Convalescence 
  • Bacterial overgrowth
  • Exocrine pancreatic insufficiency 
  • Gastritis
  • Colitis
  • Anorexia 

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pancreatitis or history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia

  HIGH ENERGY This formula is high energy reducing the amount of food given per meal.



 


HIGHLY APPETISING Dogs suffering from digestive troubles often show a decreased appetite and weight loss. The right balance of ingredients makes this diet highly appetising for dogs experiencing digestive upsets.

Mobility C2P+


Mobility C2P+ is a complete feed for dogs that helps support osteoarthritis.


For your information: Please note that the presence of orange particles on the kibble surface is completely normal; it is due to the presence of turmeric extract.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Helps maintain mobility in dogs
  • Helps support the joints after orthopaedic surgery or trauma

Not recommended for (contra-indications):


  • Puppies under 8 months
  • Lactation

 RECOMMENDATIONS: Follow your vet’s nutritional recommendations.



EXCLUSIVE JOINT COMPLEX


Formulated with the innovative C2P+ Joint Complex comprising tumeric extract, hydrolysed collagen and green tea polyphenols, nutrients known to support joint health and mobility.



SCIENTIFICALLY PROVEN


The active ingredients incorporated into the exclusive C2P+ joint complex have been shown to improve dogs' mobility and quality of life.



EASES MOBILITY MANAGEMENT


An enhanced palatability encourages consumption of vital nutrients to assist with the daily management of the clinical signs of osteoarthritis.



MODERATE CALORIE


Moderate calorie content to help maintain an ideal body weight. Excessive weight can add further strain to already stressed joints.

Mô tả:
Cardiac


Cardiac is a complete diet for adult dogs to support heart function in the case of chronic cardiac disease. This diet contains a low level of sodium and increased potassium.


Recommended for (indications):


  • Congestive cardiac failure 
  • Hypertension

Not recommended for (contraindications): 


  • Pregnancy 
  • Lactation
  • Growth
  • Hyponatraemia
  • Pancreatitis or a history of pancreatitis 
  • Hyperlipidaemia


Key Benefits:


  VASCULAR SUPPORT Supports renal filtration by helping facilitate dilation of small blood vessels in the kidneys and therefore reducing pressure in the filteration unit (the Glomerulus). 



 


  EARLY RENAL SUPPORT Heart disease often increases the work load on the kidneys. A moderate phosphorus content will help maintain renal function in dogs with heart disease.



 


  ELECTROLYTE BALANCE Includes electrolytes to support heart function as electrolyte imbalances can have a detrimental effect on the management of cardiac disease.  



 


  CARDIAC SUPPORT Taurine and L-carnitine are included to assist muscle fibre function in the heart, aiding the heart to expand and contract.

Mô tả:
Royal Canin Babydog Milk for puppies from birth to weaning.


Harmonious growth


For steady, harmonious growth, the composition of Babydog milk is as close as possible to bitch’s milk, with high energy and protein levels.


Digestive safety


Babydog milk contains carefully selected ultra-digestible proteins, and has a lactose content very close to that of maternal milk. It is particularly suitable for the puppy’s digestive system, because it does not contain starch, (puppies don’t secrete enough amylase to digest starch). Finally, the addition of Fructo-Oligo-Saccharides (FOS) helps maintain a healthy balance of digestive flora.


Easy to prepare


Thanks to its exclusive formula, Babydog milk dissolves instantly and completely, with no sediment, creating a totally homogenous formula.


Enriched with dha


The puppy’s nervous system continues to develop after birth. DHA naturally present in maternal milk helps develop cognitive function, and so Babydog milk is enriched with DHA.


Composition


Milk proteins, animal fats, whey protein, soya oil, copra oil, fish oil (source of DHA), minerals, fructo-oligo-saccharides. Crude ash: 6%. Crude fibre: 0%. Crude oil fats: 39%. Moisture: 0%. Protein: 33%.


Additives


Nutritional additives: Vitamin A: 25000 IU, Vitamin D3: 1500 IU, E1 (Iron): 100 mg, E2 (Iodine): 4 mg, E4 (Copper): 15 mg, E5 (Manganese): 80 mg, E6 (Zinc): 230 mg, E8 (Selenium): 0.43 mg, Taurine: 2.5 g - Antioxidants.


Water should be available at all times.

Mô tả:
A complete dog feed for the small breed bitch (from 1 to 10 kg) and her puppies: bitch at the end of gestation and during lactation, weaning puppies up to 2 months of age.



BIRTH PROGRAMME


Inspired by Professional research, the BIRTH PROGRAMME is a unique nutritional solution which meets the needs of the bitch and her puppies during the first five stages of their life cycle: gestation, birth, lactation, weaning, and growth up to 2 months of age.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


The fruit of ongoing science from Royal Canin, START COMPLEX is an exclusive combination of nutritional elements which are present in mother’s milk, reinforced with specific nutrients which actively contribute to promoting digestive health and supporting the puppy’s natural defences.



GESTATION/LACTATION SUPPORT


A nutritional profile which is adapted to the bitch’s high energy needs at the end of gestation and during lactation.



IDEAL FOR TRANSITION FROM MILK


A nutritional response which facilitates the transition from mother’s milk to solid food (energy value, quality protein, fats), due to the rehydratable capacity of this diets kibbles.



EASY REHYDRATION


The kibbles easily rehydrate to a porridge-like consistency which is very palatable for the bitch and her weaning puppies.

ROYAL CANIN RECOVERY là một loại thức ăn cho chó và mèo được đánh giá cao, ngon miệng, hoàn hảo và cân bằng nhằm hỗ trợ dinh dưỡng giúp phục hồi sức khỏe cho chó mèo và được sự hướng dẫn của bác sĩ thú y.


THÔNG TIN SẢN PHẨM


Lợi ích


  • Hàm lượng năng lượng của ROYAL CANIN RECOVERY giúp bù đắp sự sụt giảm lượng thức ăn đối với vật nuôi kén chọn ăn uống.
  • Kết cấu của ROYAL CANIN RECOVERY giúp việc cho ăn bằng ống tiêm hoặc ống truyền dễ dàng hơn rất nhiều.
  • EPA/DHA, Axit béo Omega-3 chuỗi dài hỗ trợ hệ tiêu hóa khỏe mạnh
  • Sự kết hợp các dưỡng chất chống oxy hóa (Vitamin E, C, tuarine, lutein) làm giảm tác động oxy hóa và giúp trung hòa các tế bào tự do.

Chỉ định


  • Biếng ăn – suy dinh dưỡng;
  • Hỗ trợ dinh dưỡng hậu phẫu thuật và chăm sóc đặc biệt;
  • Điều dưỡng;
  • Ăn bằng tube;
  • Rối loạn chuyển hóa lipid gan ở mèo;
  • Mang thai, cho con bú, tăng trưởng.

Chống chỉ định


  • Bệnh não do gan;
  • Viêm tụy cấp;
  • Hyperlipidaemia.

THÀNH PHẦN


Nguyên liệu


Thịt gà, gan gà, phụ phẩm gelatin, xenluloza bột, casein, dầu cá, hương vị tự nhiên, tetrapotassium pyrophosphate, dầu thực vật, canxi cacbonat, canxi sunfat, sản phẩm trứng khô, guar gum, sản phẩm phụ thịt lợn, Taurine, natri tripolyphosphate, clorua choline, kẹo cao su, inulin, vitamin [DL-alpha tocopherol acetate (nguồn vitamin E), L-ascorbyl-2-polyphosphate (nguồn vitamin C), thiamine mononitrat (vitamin B1), niacin bổ sung , Biotin, D-canxi pantothenate, bổ sung riboflavin (vitamin B2), pyridoxine hydrochloride (vitamin B6), bổ sung vitamin B12, axit folic, bổ sung vitamin D3>, men thủy phân, khoáng chất vết (zinc proteinate, zinc oxide, ferrous sulfate, Sunfat, oxit mangan, natri selenit, canxi iodat), chiết xuất hoa oải hương (Tagetes erecta L.), carrageenan.


Thành phần dinh dưỡng



------------------------------------------------------------


DOG AND CAT RECOVERY® CANNED FOOD 


RECOVERY là thức ăn dinh dưỡng hoàn chỉnh cho cả chó và mèo, được xây dựng để thúc đẩy việc phục hồi dinh dưỡng trong quá trình hồi sức hoặc trong trường hợp bị rối loạn chuyển hóa gan. Thức ăn này có mật độ năng lượng cao và nồng độ cao các chất dinh dưỡng thiết yếu, dễ tiêu hóa


 


Đề xuất cho (chỉ dẫn):


  • - Biếng ăn, suy dinh dưỡng
  • - Hỗ trợ dinh dưỡng trong quá trình phẫu thuật, sau phẫu thuật và chăm sóc đặc biệt
  • - Đang hồi phục
  • - Nuôi ăn bằng ống*
  • - Mang thai, tới kì sinh sản, đang tăng trưởng
  • - Cơ thể bị yếu do bệnh mãn tính hoặc các bệnh trầm trọng.
    - Chó/mèo lớn tuổi, bị chứng xơ cứng động mạch, suy nhược cơ thể, và viêm gan B và không có sự khác biệt đáng kể về tần suất các bệnh truyền nhiễm khác.

Không dùng cho (chống chỉ định):


  • - Bệnh gan
  • - Viêm tụy cấp và tăng lipid máu

Sản phẩm của Royal Canin, Pháp
Mô tả:
Được thành lập bởi các nhà khoa học và các bác sĩ thú y, ROYAL CANIN đã có hơn 40 năm kinh nghiệm trong việc nghiên cứu dinh dưỡng và sức khỏe cho vật nuôi. Công việc của chúng tôi và các nhà dinh dưỡng, lai tạo và bác sĩ thú y từ khắp nơi trên thế giới là cung cấp kiến thức và đáp ứng các nhu cầu dinh dưỡng cụ thể cho chó mèo.


  • Năng lượng cao để giảm lượng thức ăn
  • Kích thích sự thèm ăn
  • 100% dinh dưỡng cân bằng và cân bằng
  • Bảo đảm 100% mức độ hài lòng

ROYAL CANIN RECOVERY là một loại thức ăn cho chó và mèo được đánh giá cao, ngon miệng, hoàn hảo và cân bằng nhằm hỗ trợ dinh dưỡng giúp phục hồi sức khỏe cho chó mèo và được sự hướng dẫn của bác sĩ thú y.


THÔNG TIN SẢN PHẨM


Lợi ích


  • Hàm lượng năng lượng của ROYAL CANIN RECOVERY giúp bù đắp sự sụt giảm lượng thức ăn đối với vật nuôi kén chọn ăn uống.
  • Kết cấu của ROYAL CANIN RECOVERY giúp việc cho ăn bằng ống tiêm hoặc ống truyền dễ dàng hơn rất nhiều.
  • EPA/DHA, Axit béo Omega-3 chuỗi dài hỗ trợ hệ tiêu hóa khỏe mạnh
  • Sự kết hợp các dưỡng chất chống oxy hóa (Vitamin E, C, tuarine, lutein) làm giảm tác động oxy hóa và giúp trung hòa các tế bào tự do.

Chỉ định


  • Biếng ăn – suy dinh dưỡng;
  • Hỗ trợ dinh dưỡng hậu phẫu thuật và chăm sóc đặc biệt;
  • Điều dưỡng;
  • Ăn bằng tube;
  • Rối loạn chuyển hóa lipid gan ở mèo;
  • Mang thai, cho con bú, tăng trưởng.

Chống chỉ định


  • Bệnh não do gan;
  • Viêm tụy cấp;
  • Hyperlipidaemia.

THÀNH PHẦN


Nguyên liệu


Thịt gà, gan gà, phụ phẩm gelatin, xenluloza bột, casein, dầu cá, hương vị tự nhiên, tetrapotassium pyrophosphate, dầu thực vật, canxi cacbonat, canxi sunfat, sản phẩm trứng khô, guar gum, sản phẩm phụ thịt lợn, Taurine, natri tripolyphosphate, clorua choline, kẹo cao su, inulin, vitamin [DL-alpha tocopherol acetate (nguồn vitamin E), L-ascorbyl-2-polyphosphate (nguồn vitamin C), thiamine mononitrat (vitamin B1), niacin bổ sung , Biotin, D-canxi pantothenate, bổ sung riboflavin (vitamin B2), pyridoxine hydrochloride (vitamin B6), bổ sung vitamin B12, axit folic, bổ sung vitamin D3>, men thủy phân, khoáng chất vết (zinc proteinate, zinc oxide, ferrous sulfate, Sunfat, oxit mangan, natri selenit, canxi iodat), chiết xuất hoa oải hương (Tagetes erecta L.), carrageenan.


Thành phần dinh dưỡng



------------------------------------------------------------


DOG AND CAT RECOVERY® CANNED FOOD 


RECOVERY là thức ăn dinh dưỡng hoàn chỉnh cho cả chó và mèo, được xây dựng để thúc đẩy việc phục hồi dinh dưỡng trong quá trình hồi sức hoặc trong trường hợp bị rối loạn chuyển hóa gan. Thức ăn này có mật độ năng lượng cao và nồng độ cao các chất dinh dưỡng thiết yếu, dễ tiêu hóa


 


Đề xuất cho (chỉ dẫn):


  • - Biếng ăn, suy dinh dưỡng
  • - Hỗ trợ dinh dưỡng trong quá trình phẫu thuật, sau phẫu thuật và chăm sóc đặc biệt
  • - Đang hồi phục
  • - Nuôi ăn bằng ống*
  • - Mang thai, tới kì sinh sản, đang tăng trưởng
  • - Cơ thể bị yếu do bệnh mãn tính hoặc các bệnh trầm trọng.
    - Chó/mèo lớn tuổi, bị chứng xơ cứng động mạch, suy nhược cơ thể, và viêm gan B và không có sự khác biệt đáng kể về tần suất các bệnh truyền nhiễm khác.

Không dùng cho (chống chỉ định):


  • - Bệnh gan
  • - Viêm tụy cấp và tăng lipid máu
  •  

* Đối với ống mũi thực quản có đường kính nhỏ hơn 10 tiếng thì cần phải pha loãng 1 thể tích Recovery với 1 thể tích nước

Sản phẩm của Royal Canin, Pháp
Mô tả:
Được thành lập bởi các nhà khoa học và các bác sĩ thú y, ROYAL CANIN đã có hơn 40 năm kinh nghiệm trong việc nghiên cứu dinh dưỡng và sức khỏe cho vật nuôi. Công việc của chúng tôi và các nhà dinh dưỡng, lai tạo và bác sĩ thú y từ khắp nơi trên thế giới là cung cấp kiến thức và đáp ứng các nhu cầu dinh dưỡng cụ thể cho chó mèo.


  • Năng lượng cao để giảm lượng thức ăn
  • Kích thích sự thèm ăn
  • 100% dinh dưỡng cân bằng và cân bằng
  • Bảo đảm 100% mức độ hài lòng

ROYAL CANIN RECOVERY là một loại thức ăn cho chó và mèo được đánh giá cao, ngon miệng, hoàn hảo và cân bằng nhằm hỗ trợ dinh dưỡng giúp phục hồi sức khỏe cho chó mèo và được sự hướng dẫn của bác sĩ thú y.


THÔNG TIN SẢN PHẨM


Lợi ích


  • Hàm lượng năng lượng của ROYAL CANIN RECOVERY giúp bù đắp sự sụt giảm lượng thức ăn đối với vật nuôi kén chọn ăn uống.
  • Kết cấu của ROYAL CANIN RECOVERY giúp việc cho ăn bằng ống tiêm hoặc ống truyền dễ dàng hơn rất nhiều.
  • EPA/DHA, Axit béo Omega-3 chuỗi dài hỗ trợ hệ tiêu hóa khỏe mạnh
  • Sự kết hợp các dưỡng chất chống oxy hóa (Vitamin E, C, tuarine, lutein) làm giảm tác động oxy hóa và giúp trung hòa các tế bào tự do.

Chỉ định


  • Biếng ăn – suy dinh dưỡng;
  • Hỗ trợ dinh dưỡng hậu phẫu thuật và chăm sóc đặc biệt;
  • Điều dưỡng;
  • Ăn bằng tube;
  • Rối loạn chuyển hóa lipid gan ở mèo;
  • Mang thai, cho con bú, tăng trưởng.

Chống chỉ định


  • Bệnh não do gan;
  • Viêm tụy cấp;
  • Hyperlipidaemia.

THÀNH PHẦN


Nguyên liệu


Thịt gà, gan gà, phụ phẩm gelatin, xenluloza bột, casein, dầu cá, hương vị tự nhiên, tetrapotassium pyrophosphate, dầu thực vật, canxi cacbonat, canxi sunfat, sản phẩm trứng khô, guar gum, sản phẩm phụ thịt lợn, Taurine, natri tripolyphosphate, clorua choline, kẹo cao su, inulin, vitamin [DL-alpha tocopherol acetate (nguồn vitamin E), L-ascorbyl-2-polyphosphate (nguồn vitamin C), thiamine mononitrat (vitamin B1), niacin bổ sung , Biotin, D-canxi pantothenate, bổ sung riboflavin (vitamin B2), pyridoxine hydrochloride (vitamin B6), bổ sung vitamin B12, axit folic, bổ sung vitamin D3>, men thủy phân, khoáng chất vết (zinc proteinate, zinc oxide, ferrous sulfate, Sunfat, oxit mangan, natri selenit, canxi iodat), chiết xuất hoa oải hương (Tagetes erecta L.), carrageenan.


Thành phần dinh dưỡng



------------------------------------------------------------


DOG AND CAT RECOVERY® CANNED FOOD 


RECOVERY là thức ăn dinh dưỡng hoàn chỉnh cho cả chó và mèo, được xây dựng để thúc đẩy việc phục hồi dinh dưỡng trong quá trình hồi sức hoặc trong trường hợp bị rối loạn chuyển hóa gan. Thức ăn này có mật độ năng lượng cao và nồng độ cao các chất dinh dưỡng thiết yếu, dễ tiêu hóa


 


Đề xuất cho (chỉ dẫn):


  • - Biếng ăn, suy dinh dưỡng
  • - Hỗ trợ dinh dưỡng trong quá trình phẫu thuật, sau phẫu thuật và chăm sóc đặc biệt
  • - Đang hồi phục
  • - Nuôi ăn bằng ống*
  • - Mang thai, tới kì sinh sản, đang tăng trưởng
  • - Cơ thể bị yếu do bệnh mãn tính hoặc các bệnh trầm trọng.
    - Chó/mèo lớn tuổi, bị chứng xơ cứng động mạch, suy nhược cơ thể, và viêm gan B và không có sự khác biệt đáng kể về tần suất các bệnh truyền nhiễm khác.

Không dùng cho (chống chỉ định):


  • - Bệnh gan
  • - Viêm tụy cấp và tăng lipid máu
  •  

* Đối với ống mũi thực quản có đường kính nhỏ hơn 10 tiếng thì cần phải pha loãng 1 thể tích Recovery với 1 thể tích nước

Reheat to blood temperature before feeding young animals. Always keep fresh drinking water available.
Recommended dilution: Add 30g (12 level scoops) to every 105ml warm water (165g should be added to a pint of water). One level scoop is approximately 2.5g Lactol powder.
Recommended daily dosage: It is impossible to give precise daily quantities due to considerable variations of age
Mã sản phẩm: therefore “demand feeding” will often be your best guide.

Tên: give Lactol milk as an additional feed to weaker youngsters.

ID: Quantity as a complementary feed for weaned pups:
• 5 - 8 weeks of age: up to 4.0% of the body weight = 40 ml/kg.
• 8 - 52 weeks of age: up to 1.1% of the body weight = 11 ml/kg.
Quantity as a complementary feed for growing or adult animals:
• Pregnant or lactating mother animals: up to 1.1% of the body weight = 11 ml/kg.
• Convalescent or sick animals: up to 1.1% of the body weight = 11 ml/kg.

ID: The use of clean sterile feeding equipment is highly recommended
Prepared feed may be kept in a refrigerator for up to 24 hours.
Reheat to blood temperature before feeding young animals. Always keep fresh drinking water available.
Recommended dilution: Add 30g (12 level scoops) to every 105ml warm water (165g should be added to a pint of water). One level scoop is approximately 2.5g Lactol powder.
Recommended daily dosage: It is impossible to give precise daily quantities due to considerable variations of age
Mã sản phẩm: therefore “demand feeding” will often be your best guide.

Loại: but still with their mother: If the youngster is completely pushed away by siblings or rejected by the mother
Mã sản phẩm: switch to the dosage for orphaned animals. In other cases
Tên: give Lactol milk as an additional feed to weaker youngsters.

ID: Quantity as a complementary feed for weaned pups:
• 5 - 8 weeks of age: up to 4.0% of the body weight = 40 ml/kg.
• 8 - 52 weeks of age: up to 1.1% of the body weight = 11 ml/kg.
Quantity as a complementary feed for growing or adult animals:
• Pregnant or lactating mother animals: up to 1.1% of the body weight = 11 ml/kg.
• Convalescent or sick animals: up to 1.1% of the body weight = 11 ml/kg.

Mô tả:
Vòng trị ve rận Killtix size M 48cm


Hoạt chất: Propoxur: 10 %, Flumethrin: 2,25 %

Bảo vệ thú cưng khỏi ve và bọ chét kéo dài đến 7 tháng
Cách đeo vòng Kiltix® cho chó


  • 1. Lấy vòng Kiltix® khỏi túi bảo vệ, tháo ra và lấy vòng nhựa bên trong.

    2. Kéo vòng ra.

    3. Đeo vòng quanh cổ chó và kéo đầu tự do luồn vào khóa. Chừa trống khoảng 2 ngón tay giữa vòng Kiltix® và cổ chó.

    4. Đối với chó nhỏ, cắt phần dư của vòng và gói phần cắt ra vào giấy và vứt bỏ. Đối với giống chó lớn, dễ dàng để nối 2 vòng với nhau.

    5. Nên đeo vòng Kiltix® liên tục. Thay vòng mới sau 5 – 6 tháng hoặc sớm hơn khi thấy hiệu quả của vòng giảm.

Tiện lợi, dễ sử dụng và an toàn cho chó con trên 3 tháng tuổi, chó mang thai và cho con bú

Quy cách:


  • Vòng đeo Kiltix® cho chó dưới 20 kg: dài 48 cm, nặng 30,2 gram.
  • Vòng đeo Kiltix® cho chó trên 20 kg: dài 66 cm, nặng 45 gram.

Điều trị nhiễm giun tròn trên chó con dưới 1 năm tuổi
Cho một liều đơn: 1ml sản phẩm/kg thể trọng (tương đương 15 mg febantel/kg thể trọng và 5 mg pyrantel/ kg thể trọng).
Giun đũa truyền qua nhau thai và sữa
Loại: nên có thể xuất hiện ở chó còn non. Đối với một vài loài chó
Mã sản phẩm: đặc biệt trong trường hợp nhiễm nặng
Tên: rất khó tẩy hết giun đũa và không thể loại trừ nguy cơ lây nhiễm cho người. Tùy tình hình dịch tễ có thể bắt đầu điều trị lúc 2 tuần tuổi và lặp lại vào những khoảng thời gian thích hợp (ví dụ mỗi 2 tuần) cho đến khi cai sữa và/hoặc điều trị dựa trên kết quả kiểm tra phân.

ID: Đường cấp thuốc: Cấp thuốc bằng đường uống. Có thể cho chó uống trực tiếp hay trộn vào thức ăn. Không cần chế độ ăn đặc biệt. Lắc đều dung dịch trước khi rút thuốc khỏi chai và sử dụng.
CHỐNG CHỈ ĐỊNH: Không dùng cho chó mẹ mang thai và cho con bú. Không dùng đồng thời với hợp chất chứa piperazine.
TÁC DỤNG KHÔNG MONG MUỐN: Rất ít xảy ra các triệu chứng nhẹ trên đường tiêu hóa (như: ói
Loại: tiêu chảy). Nếu thấy bất kì tác dụng phụ nào không được liệt kê trong toa thuốc này
Mã sản phẩm: xin hãy liên hệ với bác sĩ thú y.

ID: BẢO QUẢN: Thuốc chưa mở bảo quản ở nhiệt độ phòng (dưới 30oC). Sau khi mở
Loại: bảo quản thuốc ở nhiệt độ không quá 25OC.

Bảo vệ thú cưng khỏi ve và bọ chét kéo dài đến 7 tháng
Cách đeo vòng Kiltix® cho chó


  • 1. Lấy vòng Kiltix® khỏi túi bảo vệ, tháo ra và lấy vòng nhựa bên trong.

    2. Kéo vòng ra.

    3. Đeo vòng quanh cổ chó và kéo đầu tự do luồn vào khóa. Chừa trống khoảng 2 ngón tay giữa vòng Kiltix® và cổ chó.

    4. Đối với chó nhỏ, cắt phần dư của vòng và gói phần cắt ra vào giấy và vứt bỏ. Đối với giống chó lớn, dễ dàng để nối 2 vòng với nhau.

    5. Nên đeo vòng Kiltix® liên tục. Thay vòng mới sau 5 – 6 tháng hoặc sớm hơn khi thấy hiệu quả của vòng giảm.

Tiện lợi, dễ sử dụng và an toàn cho chó con trên 3 tháng tuổi, chó mang thai và cho con bú

Quy cách:


  • Vòng đeo Kiltix® cho chó dưới 20 kg: dài 48 cm, nặng 30,2 gram.
  • Vòng đeo Kiltix® cho chó trên 20 kg: dài 66 cm, nặng 45 gram.

ID: Trên chó: thuốc có tác dụng trên ve trong 04 tuần và trên bọ chét trong 02 tháng (từ 1-3 tháng tùy thuộc mức độ ký sinh trùng trong môi trường).
Trên mèo: thuốc có tác dụng trên bọ chét trong 06 tuần.
Xịt toàn bộ cơ thể thú và giữ bình xịt cách thú từ 10 – 20 cm. Vuốt ngược lông thú từ sau ra trước để lông thú đứng và đảm bảo xịt ướt toàn bộ cơ thể thú. Đặc biệt đối với thú có bộ lông dài
Loại: cần vuốt gợn sóng bộ lông thú để thuốc ngấm tới da. Kế đó để da thú khô tự nhiên. Không lau khô.

ID: Mang găng tay khi chữa trị cho thú.
Xịt cho thú ở nơi thông thoáng tốt.
Rửa sạch tay sau khi xịt thuốc.
Giữ thú tránh xa lửa hay các nguồn nhiệt khác trong 30 phút khi đã điều trị bằng thuốc cho đến khi bộ lông khô hoàn toàn.
BẢO QUẢN: Bảo quản ở nhiệt độ dưới 25°C. Tránh xa tầm tay trẻ em

Bảo vệ thú cưng khỏi ve và bọ chét kéo dài đến 7 tháng
Cách đeo vòng Kiltix® cho chó


  • 1. Lấy vòng Kiltix® khỏi túi bảo vệ, tháo ra và lấy vòng nhựa bên trong.

    2. Kéo vòng ra.

    3. Đeo vòng quanh cổ chó và kéo đầu tự do luồn vào khóa. Chừa trống khoảng 2 ngón tay giữa vòng Kiltix® và cổ chó.

    4. Đối với chó nhỏ, cắt phần dư của vòng và gói phần cắt ra vào giấy và vứt bỏ. Đối với giống chó lớn, dễ dàng để nối 2 vòng với nhau.

    5. Nên đeo vòng Kiltix® liên tục. Thay vòng mới sau 5 – 6 tháng hoặc sớm hơn khi thấy hiệu quả của vòng giảm.

Tiện lợi, dễ sử dụng và an toàn cho chó con trên 3 tháng tuổi, chó mang thai và cho con bú

Quy cách:


  • Vòng đeo Kiltix® cho chó dưới 20 kg: dài 48 cm, nặng 30,2 gram.
  • Vòng đeo Kiltix® cho chó trên 20 kg: dài 66 cm, nặng 45 gram.

Mô tả: điều trị hay kiểm soát các loại ký sinh trùng ở chó để làm giảm cơ hội tiếp xúc với con người và để giữ cho chó của bạn khỏe mạnh.

Trạng thái thuế: giúp cho bộ lông thú cưng của bạn ngày càng <strong style=""margin: 0px; padding: 0px; outline: none; list-style: none;"">bóng đẹp
Còn hàng?: đồng thời dung dịch còn có mùi hương thơm nhẹ nhàng tự nhiên làm cho thú cưng của bạn sảng khoái
Kho: thích thú và làm cho ngôi nhà của bạn không còn những mùi khó chịu của động vật.

Đã đăng: sans-serif; line-height: 18px; text-align: justify;"">Dầu gội và xả cho chó lông trắng Budle’Budle Ecoland White Shampoo & Rinse rất dễ dàng sử dụng
Nhãn nổi bật?: hoà một lượng dầu gội và xả cho chó lông trắng vừa đủ vào khoảng 100ml nước
Hiển thị trong danh mục: sau khi làm ướt toàn thân của thú cưng bằng nước ấm
Mô tả ngắn: bạn xoa đều dầu gội và xả lên toàn thân thú cưng
Mô tả: chà xát nhẹ nhàng để tạo bọt và rửa sạch các vết bẩn rồi xả lại bằng nước ấm cho đến khi hết bọt xà phòng. Làm khô lông thú cưng bằng khăn và máy sấy. Sản phẩm sẽ giúp cho thú cưng của bạn có hương thơm nhẹ nhàng và bộ lông không còn khô
